archived.description: If the project is currently archived, this property is true.

creationTime.description: Not documented, but it seems to be the creation time in milliseconds since the epoch

icon.description: Not documented, but looks like a base64 encoded image that is used as the icon for this project in the GUI.

iconUrl.description: Not documented, but looks like an url for downloading the icon image

id.description: The id of this hubproject. This is the id that the 'ringId' attribute in the 'projects' datatype refer to.

key.description: Not documented, but looks like it is the same as the 'shortName' property in the 'projects' datatype.

id.description: The id of the organization this project belongs to (if any)
Not documented, but seems to be the id of the user that owns this project.
Not documented, but seems to be the id of a 'projectroles' instance, which is used for assigning roles on this project to users
Not documented, but seem to be a way to differ between different project types. I've only seen the value 'DEFAULT'

name.description: Not documented, but seem to be a way to differ between different project types. I've only seen the value 'Default'

id.description: Not documented, but seems to refer to the id of an instanse of the 'projectteams' datatype
